  "description": "# SoC AHB-to-APB bridge timing closure\n\nYou're the timing lead on a chip tapeout. The AHB-to-APB bus bridge block is failing timing at 800 MHz (1.25 ns period). The worst violation is **-310 ps** on the write-data path from `ahb_wrdata_reg[7]/Q` through the protocol state machine decode logic, through crossbar ECC logic, and into `apb_wdata_reg[3]/D`.\n\nThe synthesizer was told to pipeline this path but ran out of area budget — so the full combinational depth remains in a single cycle. Multiple factors compound:\n- The decode logic is deep (4 levels: AND → OR → NAND → INV)\n- A high-fanout net fans out to 4 loads through a weak buffer\n- Wire delays on a long route between AHB and APB flop banks are significant\n- The clock tree has asymmetric insertion delay between the two domains\n\nPost-CTS, post-route. Uncertainty is 40 ps.\n\nYou have a full command palette. There is no silver-bullet fix — you'll need to understand every contributor before choosing.\n\n**Target:** close timing with minimum PPA cost.",
